Package: dpm.lpa
Type: Package
Title: Dirichlet Process Mixture Latent Profile Analysis
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Sam Paskewitz
Maintainer: Sam Paskewitz <samuel.paskewitz@yale.edu>
Description: Performs a type of Bayesian latent profile analysis (LPA) that 
    automatically infers the number of latent profiles. In particular, it
    implements variational Bayes estimation of the Dirichlet process mixture
    model, hence the name DPM-LPA.
Config/reticulate/autoconfigure:
  list(
    packages = list(
      list(package = "numpy"),
      list(package = "pandas"),
      list(package = "scipy"),
      list(package = "plotnine", pip = TRUE),
      list(package = "vbayesfa", pip = TRUE)
    )
  )
License: What license is it under?
Depends: 
    R (>= 2.10),
    reticulate
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Suggests: 
    knitr,
    rmarkdown
VignetteBuilder: knitr
